Ad Text:
Lead the development, implementation, and optimisation of advanced digital phenotyping platforms, including multimodal sensing, spectral data workflows, and FAIR-complaint data pipelines.
Work within a collaborative, cutting-edge research environment at UWA.
Full-time (1.0 FTE) appointment on a fixed term basis for 2 years.
Base salary range: $116,262 – $127,078 p.a. plus 17% superannuation.

About the opportunity

Apply cutting-edge data science, computer vision, deep learning, and generative AI to agricultural and phenomics research across UWA, DPIRD, and national APPN partners.
Coordinate end-to-end field data operations and provide technical leadership, training, and community-of-practice engagement across APPN nodes and end-users.
This role is offered within the UWA Professional staff stream, at an equivalent pay rate and level to Academic Stream Level B (Lecturer/Research Fellow). This is to encourage both postdoctoral-level researchers with a PhD, or industry-experienced and tertiary-qualified data science professionals to apply for this role.

About you

You have strong experience in Python and/or R, Unix/Linux, version control, and engineering scalable, production-ready data pipelines.
You bring expertise in remote sensing and multimodal data processing (RGB, multispectral, hyperspectral, LiDAR) from drone/robotic/satellite platforms.
You have demonstrated capability in deep learning, computer vision, and emerging generative AI approaches in agricultural or phenomics applications.
You understand FAIR data principles and have experience designing workflows, metadata, and data governance practices that ensure reproducibility and high-quality research outputs.
You are an excellent communicator with a track record in stakeholder engagement, training delivery, technical documentation, and collaborative problem-solving across diverse research and industry settings.

Special Requirements

Employment checks will include information on gender-based violence, sexual harassment, and related misconduct to meet legal obligations.
Some after-hours work may be required.
Current “C” class driver’s licence desirable.
Certified 4WD training and First Aid Certificate are highly desirable, or a willingness to undertake training.
Current CASA Remote Pilot License (RePL) for <25kg Multirotor and Aviation Radio Operators Certificate (AROC) are desirable, or a willingness to undertake training.

Position description:  POSITION DESCRIPTION - Senior Data Scientist (522682).docx

To learn more about this opportunity, please contact Professor Nik Callow at nik.callow@uwa.edu.au

How to apply

Please apply online via the Apply Now button. The content of your Resume and Cover Letter should demonstrate how you meet the selection criteria.

Closing date: 11:55 PM AWST on Sunday 1st March 2026.

This position is only open to applicants with relevant rights to work in Australia.

Please note: Unsolicited applications from recruitment agencies will not be accepted outside of formal channels.

 About the University

The University of Western Australia (UWA) is ranked among the top 100 universities in the world and a member of the prestigious Australian Group of Eight research intensive universities. With a strong research track record, vibrant campus and working environments, there is no better time to join Western Australia’s top university.

Learn more about us.

Our commitment to inclusion and diversity

UWA is committed to a diverse workforce and an equitable and inclusive workplace. We are committed to fostering a safe environment for all, including Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander people, women, those from culturally and linguistically diverse backgrounds, the LGBTIQA+ community, and people living with disability.

If you require any reasonable adjustments, we encourage you to advise us at the time of application. Alternatively, you can contact us for assistance during the recruitment process.

Our client is currently seeking a Data Business Analyst to help deliver a sector-wide data roadmap that has been established to build data capability, introduce consistent reporting, and improve governance.

In this role, you will help deliver the roadmap by improving the Department’s ability to measure outcomes, understand service impact, and identify gaps and emerging needs. Your work will provide reliable evidence to inform commissioning and guide sector reform, ultimately improving safety and outcomes for women and children.You will lead initiatives that uplift data capability across a service system, including developing consistent data standards, improving data quality, and strengthening governance to support the transition to outcomes‑based reporting.

As the Data Business Analyst, you will:

Work in a team to lead the implementation of the data roadmap, ensuring coordinated delivery across interdependent workstreams.
Establish foundational data elements, including a data quality strategy, data collection standards, sector‑wide data governance mechanisms, and practical supports to strengthen data culture and capability.
Standardise data for reporting, including validation of outcome indicators, development of a revised administrative dataset, review of risk and safety methodologies to support comparable reporting, and creation of minimum system specifications to guide consistent data capture across agencies and providers.
Co‑design processes with Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander stakeholders, ensuring all work aligns with the Framework for Action.
Connect data and information flows across the system to improve insights and drive service efficiency, including linking prevalence, social and demand data to track victim‑survivor experiences over time.
Establish mechanisms to monitor client safety and perpetrator interventions, enabling more informed service responses and system coordination.
Support uplift of data culture and capability across the sector and government partners.
What you’ll bring to the role:

Minimum 5-8 years’ experience in data transformation, analytics or business improvement within the social services, community sector, justice or human services system.
You hold a relevant tertiary qualification in Business, Data Analytics, Statistics, Computer Science, or another discipline demonstrating strong analytical capability.
Strong capability in business analysis, including problem definition, requirements gathering, and identification of evidence‑based options.
Demonstrated experience leading or contributing to change initiatives involving process improvement, systems redesign or data capability uplift.
Ability to plan, coordinate and deliver complex projects, including management of interdependent workstreams.
Experience engaging and collaborating with diverse stakeholders, including sector partners, government agencies and senior leaders.
Strong analytical, conceptual and critical thinking skills, with the ability to translate data insights into practical recommendations.
Experience applying structured change management approaches to support adoption and capability uplift.

Participate in the development of the Cyber Security Plan and Roadmap to proactively address emerging threats and align with strategic objectives. This includes supplementary security strategies such as audit logging, identity and access management, digital forensics.
Support the development and implementation of a Cyber Security Capability Model as the single reference point describing the breadth, depth and state of the cybersecurity capabilities across people, processes, and technologies.
Partner with stakeholders to deliver strategic guidance and direction as part of supporting strategies, plans and roadmaps, in line with the Cyber Security Plan and Roadmap.

Our Ideal Job Seeker

Demonstrates performance and competency levels commensurate with the following Skills Framework for the Information Age (SFIA) skills:
o Enterprise and business architecture (STPL) Level 5
o Strategic planning (ITSP) Level 5
o Measurement (MEAS) Level 5
o Risk management (BURM) Level 5
Understands key cyber and security frameworks, or can quickly learn them, including the Information Security manual (ISM), Protective Security Policy Framework (PSPF), Australian Cyber Security Centre's (ACSC) Essential Eight, as well as ISO 27001, NIST Cybersecurity Framework.
Brings experience in strategic design, enterprise and business architecture, with the ability to translate complex concepts and identified opportunities into practical outcomes.
Builds strong relationships across technical and business areas, identifying requirements and gaps, addressing these and influencing stakeholders to achieve shared strategic goals.
Demonstrates strong leadership and judgement, managing multiple priorities, navigating ambiguity, and keeping executives and key stakeholders informed and engaged.
Familiar with technologies and ICT landscapes and challenges within large organisations, as well as knowledge of contemporary technologies and concepts such as artificial intelligence, and quantum computing.



Role Based in Canberra or Adelaide
Must hold Baseline Clearance

Job Title: Head of Financial Planning & Analysis - APAC
Ad Text:
Reliance Worldwide Corporation (RWC)

Plumbing Matters. We make it better. Our innovative products, built on a tradition of excellence, serve markets across plumbing, heating and construction to make our customers’ lives easier, while sustainably delivering unrivalled returns.  We are publicly listed on the Australian stock exchange (ASX) and headquartered in Atlanta, Georgia, USA with regional headquarters in Brisbane, Australia and London, UK.  Our global family of trusted brands are committed to making a positive, lasting impact – we are better for our planet and better for our people.  We operate in 45 facilities across 20 countries. We’re acquisitive and we’re laser focused on growth.

Our Culture

We’re big enough to make a difference and small enough for each one of us to make an impact.  Our culture encourages our people to think differently, challenge the status quo and shape the world around us.  Our values drive how we work together, as one global team. We have something special here – not just what we do, but who we are. We're not afraid to try new things; we punch above our weight; and we move with speed. We embrace governance but reject bureaucracy or anything that slows us down.  Our strategy ensures we provide a safe environment for our people and we actively promote diversity and inclusion.  Everyone at RWC makes a valuable contribution to our business.  Sound like somewhere you could call home?  Read on.

Are you looking for a role where you can partner with senior leaders on the direction of the business? Are you curious about what’s going in the industry and with our competitors? Are you a true business partner that is itching to make a difference to a business that it rapidly growing? Then we would love to hear from you.

About the role:

This is a newly created role in the Asia Pacific region reporting to the Chief Financial Officer, Asia Pacific. We are looking for an experienced FP&A Leader preferably with manufacturing/FMCG experience who can mentor a senior team and drive development of financial modelling. Effectively communicate and oversee financial performance, strategic plans, budgets, and forecasts. This position requires business partnership and communication with senior leadership and will lead financial planning and analysis of projects of varying nature and complexity with limited supervision. This may include analysis of the industry and competition, scenario planning, customer/channel profitability, continuous improvement, and return on investments.

Based in Eagle Farm in Brisbane, you will be responsible for partnering with the APAC teams providing reporting, analysis and business insights. This may also include pricing oversight and customer incentive management. At RWC we operate as one global team, so you will be part of a broader group of finance professionals located in the UK and USA.

You will enjoy being innovative and thinking outside the box and be comfortable to respectfully challenge the norm.

What you will need to do:

Play a leading role in guiding the FP&A team to prepare financial forecasts, reporting, and variance analysis for the region

Lead finance builds of the strategic plan, annual budget, and rolling forecasts

Develop and maintain tools and processes in place to effectively prepare financial reporting

Communicate results and forecasts effectively inside and outside of the finance team, clearly articulating drivers behind reported variances to budget, forecast, and prior periods

Partner with senior leaders to interpret results, provide insights and recommendations

Liaise with the broader finance team to facilitate period-closing processes

Prepare ad hoc analysis to evaluate business cases, scenario outcomes and capex requests.

Lead and participate in strategic initiatives identified as part of strategic planning process

Partner with sales team and S&OP team to prepare detailed forecasts of revenue and gross margin

Ensure sales team is equipped with appropriate tools and reporting to make informed decisions

Evaluate customer and product margin regularly, providing analysis and recommendations

About you:

You will bring the highest level of personal integrity and ethics

Have a commercial mindset and demonstrated high analytical skills and the ability to think strategically

Leadership experience of teams consisting of senior finance professionals

Great communicator who thrives on building relationships internally and externally

You will hold a CA or CPA qualification

10+ years of accounting, finance, or related experience in manufacturing or FMCG

Experience overseeing budget builds, forecasting, and reporting.

Ability to develop a deep understanding of the business and its key drivers

Strong analytical, problem-solving, conceptual, and critical-thinking skills

Advanced financial modelling and MS Excel skills

Experience with SAP, SAP Analytics Cloud, OneStream and Phocus is a plus

Manage competing priorities under pressure

APPLY NOW! Send a cover letter telling us about you and why this role is the one for you, along with your resume.

We are seeking a Financial Planning & Analysis Manager for a newly created role, a commercially astute leader who will set the benchmark for excellence in delivering actionable insights, driving performance improvement, and achieving strong commercial outcomes for the Group. This position offers the opportunity to make a lasting impact and define what 'good' looks like within our FP&A function with initially a very hands on approach, leading an experienced analyst to enhance our approach to business partnering and financial analysis.  

Reporting to the Deputy CFO this role will take ownership of FP&A function budgeting, forecasting and performance analysis for the Group. You're a CA or CPA qualified finance professional with significant leadership experience in FP&A with a commercial mindset. 

Key responsibilities include  

Lead and elevate the Group FP&A function across budgeting, forecasting, reporting and performance analysis 

Deliver insightful and strategic recommendations that influence business performance  

Drive cashflow forecasting/planning, working capital optimisation, and liquidity management with precision 

Own the preparation of board packs, executive reporting, and in-depth performance analysis 

Act as the key liaison for board-level financial queries and support the finance leadership in board communications. 

Lead finance system related projects and implementation programs to enhance capability and efficiency 

Strengthen governance, controls and documentation across models and reporting frameworks 

You’re a great candidate if you are 

CA or CPA qualified with strong leadership experience in FP&A 

Have a background in Retail or FMCG environments 

Hold advanced financial modelling capability, including scenario analysis, cash flow modelling and investment appraisal. 

Experience in Leading the implementation of ERP/major financial system projects  

A sharp analytical mindset, attention to detail and confidence working with large complex data sets 

Strong stakeholder engagement and influencing skills  

What’s on offer 

Direct exposure to senior finance leaders and the Board 

Flexible working arrangements 

Ongoing learning and development opportunities 

Generous team member discount 

Paid parental leave 

Employee Assistance Program 

Discounted health insurance 


Apply today if this role is for you.

About the Company
Australian Naval Infrastructure (ANI) is a Commonwealth-owned enterprise driving the future of Australia’s naval shipbuilding. Based at Osborne, South Australia, ANI develops and manages world-class infrastructure supporting major defence programs, including the Hunter-class frigates and AUKUS nuclear-powered submarines.
ANI play a vital role in delivering cutting-edge facilities that enable sovereign shipbuilding, industry growth, and national security. Join ANI and help build the future of Australia’s naval capability.


Role Overview
ANI is establishing a dedicated Data Governance Lead, to shape and embed a modern, fit-for-purpose data and information governance framework across the organisation and within ANI’s Nuclear Stewardship function focused on uplifting ANI’s capability to levels required to operate under a nuclear licensed premises. This role sits within the Information Management function and is responsible for building the standards, processes, and practices that ensure ANI’s data, documents, and records are trusted, well-managed, and compliant.
As the Data Governance Lead, you will play a critical part in strengthening how ANI captures, controls, and uses information by supporting confident decision-making, regulatory and defence sector obligations, and the long term preservation of information of national significance. You will work across structured data environments and document rich settings, partnering closely with business stakeholders to uplift capability, embed consistent practices, and provide oversight of data quality, metadata, and compliance.
This is an exciting opportunity to shape a new function, influence how data governance operates end-to-end, and contribute to ANI’s readiness for AI governance, metadata management, and future enterprise information initiatives.


Key Responsibilities:

Lead the development and implementation of ANI’s data governance framework, including policies, standards, and stewardship models.

Define and maintain data ownership and accountability across the organisation.

Embed data governance into business processes by working closely with Information Management, business areas, ICT, and external partners.

Oversee data quality, integrity, security, and lifecycle management to meet legislative, archival, and government requirements.

Manage metadata, classification, and business terminology to ensure consistent, discoverable information assets.

Monitor governance compliance and risks, providing advice and reporting to senior stakeholders.

Support Export Control obligations through effective data traceability and reporting.

Build organisational capability through tools, guidance, training, and awareness activities.



Required Skills, Knowledge and Experience



Australian citizenship and ability to obtain/maintain NV1 security clearance.

Proven experience in data or information governance, information/records management, or related fields—ideally in Defence, infrastructure, or government environments.

Strong capability in metadata, data cataloguing, data quality, and integrity management, including familiarity with compliance requirements such as Export Control and NAA standards.

Experience with Microsoft data and governance toolsets, particularly Microsoft Purview, Fabric, and Power BI.

Excellent analytical, documentation, stakeholder engagement, and communication skills, with the ability to guide and support staff across the business.

Highly organised, detail-focused, proactive, and improvement oriented, with the ability to manage competing priorities.

Tertiary qualifications and/or professional certifications (e.g., DAMA) are highly regarded.


Culture of the business:
A collaborative and compliance-driven workplace with a strong focus on digital safety, strategic innovation, and stakeholder engagement. You'll be supported by forward-thinking leaders in a culture that values transparency, continuous improvement, and resilience.

For more information, please contact Bianca Holmes on Bianca.Holmes@harrisonmcmillan.com.au

Company Overview

Centurion is a premier logistics company with a long-standing reputation for excellence in transportation services across Australia. Founded in 1971, our business provides nationwide service with 34 branches across Western Australia, Queensland, Northern Territory, New South Wales, South Australia and Victoria.

At Centurion, we are committed to safety, operational excellence and continuous improvement. As we continue to grow and transform, we are investing in analytics, technology and performance capability to enable smarter, data-driven decision making across our operations.




The Opportunity

This is a high-impact role focused on strengthening operational performance through analytics, insight and structured business analysis.

You will act as a critical bridge between Operations, Technology and Data teams - translating complex business needs into clear analytical, system and process solutions. The role combines performance analytics, stakeholder leadership and end-to-end business analysis to ensure initiatives deliver measurable business value.




Key Responsibilities

Analytics & Performance Enablement

Design, build and maintain operational dashboards, reports and self-service analytics aligned to business priorities

Analyse operational performance trends, risks and opportunities, translating data into actionable insights

Conduct deep-dive analysis to identify root causes, performance drivers and improvement opportunities

Partner with operational leaders to define meaningful KPIs, metrics and data standards

Ensure data accuracy, integrity and consistency across reporting outputs

Drive continuous improvement through insight-led recommendations and measurable outcomes




Stakeholder Leadership, Business–Technology Translation & Continuous Improvement

Act as a bridge between operational stakeholders and technology delivery teams

Ensure solutions align to business outcomes, operational usability, scalability and compliance requirements

Validate delivered solutions meet operational intent and deliver measurable value

Act as a trusted advisor to operational leaders and project stakeholders

Build strong cross-functional relationships across Operations, IT, Data, Finance and Transformation teams

Partner with Data Analytics to align KPI frameworks, definitions and reporting standards

Communicate complex insights clearly to both technical and non-technical audiences

Maintain governance artefacts, documentation standards and traceability

Drive maturity in analytics, reporting and business analysis practices

Promote data literacy and insight-led decision making across the business

Identify opportunities for automation, system optimisation and process digitisation




Business Analysis & Solution Delivery

Lead end-to-end business analysis across operational and technology initiatives

Elicit, document and validate business requirements, functional specifications and acceptance criteria

Map current and future state processes, identifying inefficiencies, risks and control gaps

Translate operational needs into clear system, data and process requirements

Support solution design, prioritisation, delivery planning and implementation readiness

Contribute to business cases, benefits realisation tracking and post-implementation optimisation




Skills & Experience

5+ years’ experience in Business Analytics, Data Analytics or Business Transformation roles

Strong operational reporting and performance analytics capability

Outcome-focused mindset with proven ability to translate analysis into tangible business value

Critical thinking and structured problem-solving skills

High-level communication and presentation skills across technical and non-technical audiences

Strong stakeholder facilitation, workshop leadership and change support capability

Strong governance discipline including documentation standards, traceability and risk awareness

Desirable:

Strong SQL and Python capability

Experience with modern data stack tools (Snowflake, dbt, Fivetran)

Experience in continuous improvement, Lean or process optimisation frameworks




Why Join Centurion?

Be part of a national organisation investing in analytics and transformation capability

Influence operational performance across a large-scale logistics network

Work cross-functionally with senior operational and technology leaders

Opportunity to shape KPI frameworks, reporting standards and analytics maturity

Career growth within a fast-growing, values-driven organisation

Supportive leadership team focused on continuous improvement and innovation




How to Apply:

If you are a commercially minded analyst who thrives on turning data into insight and insight into measurable outcomes, we want to hear from you.

Click Apply Now to take the next step in your career with Centurion or contact recruitment@centurion.net.au for more information.

Centurion is an Equal Opportunity employer. We encourage applications from women and First Nations People.

Please note we do not accept applications from recruitment agencies. Direct applicants only.

Ad Text:
About this Opportunity

Continuing, Full-Time

Commercial Services

CQUniversity Rockhampton

Higher Education Worker Level 8

Total Remuneration $135,403 to $150,810 pa (including salary of $114,418 to $127,437 plus 17% superannuation and leave loading)

Join an organisation with an unbreakable belief that quality education, training and research should be available to everyone – regardless of background, location or life circumstances.

Working at CQUniversity

The Commercial Services Directorate drives the University’s commercial and student residential services portfolio to support performance and strategic growth, leading initiatives across business development, financial planning, governance, and operational performance. The Directorate partners closely with internal and external stakeholders to deliver sustainable commercial outcomes that support CQUniversity’s long term vision.

As the Executive Officer, you will work closely with the Director - Commercial Services to provide high level strategic advice, analytical insight, and executive support. You will lead complex projects, prepare business cases and financial analyses, coordinate governance and committee processes, and contribute to strategic and budget planning. Acting as a trusted adviser, you will engage confidently with senior leaders and external stakeholders, exercising sound judgement in complex and sensitive matters.

We are seeking a commercially astute, politically savvy professional with extensive experience in strategy, governance and financial analysis. If you thrive in a fast-paced environment where influence, initiative and impact matter, this is your opportunity to help shape CQUniversity’s commercial future.

Be Rewarded

17% superannuation (with the choice to join an award-winning superfund)

6 weeks annual leave (incl. Christmas and New Year closure)

10 days personal/sick leave, plus 5 days carer’s leave

7.25 hours engaged service leave

Fantastic professional and career development opportunities

Up to 26 weeks (six months) paid parental leave

Access to an Employee Assistance Program and Fitness Passport

Position Requirements

Strong organisational and time-management skills, with the ability to prioritise competing tasks effectively.

Experience leading or supporting teams, with demonstrated ability to mentor and develop staff.

Ability to adapt quickly to changing priorities and work effectively under pressure.

Knowledge of compliance, governance, and risk management principles relevant to the role.

Commitment to continuous improvement and professional development.

Postgraduate qualifications with extensive relevant experience, or significant professional and management experience, or an equivalent combination of education and experience.

For further information about this position, please refer to the Position Description on the CQUniversity Careers Site.

Applications Close: 11:59pm, Wednesday, 11 March 2026

Job Requisition ID: 7031

When submitting your application, please include: Your Current CV or Resume, and a 1-2 page Cover Letter highlighting your relevant skills, experience and suitability for the position.

Work Rights: Visa sponsorship is not available for this position. Candidates must hold the full rights to work in Australia to be considered for this appointment.

CQUniversity is an equal opportunity employer and welcomes diversity in the workplace. Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander people, and CQUniversity’s domestic and international student graduates with post-study work rights are encouraged to apply.

The Company:

A leading Australian brand is looking for a PowerBI Developer contractor to work on business critical initiatives within their enterprise environment. You must be Sydney based and able to work in the office 3 days per week. This role is for an initial 6 months with the potential to be extended.

The Role:


Strong stakeholder engagement, with the ability to communicate with both non-technical and technical stakeholders including taking requirements and translating into Power BI solutions.
Develop PowerBI dashboards from business requirements and functional design documents, end user manuals and business glossaries.
Regular and effective internal customer engagement to build strong partnerships with stakeholders.
Collaboration with business units and cross-functional teams responsible for IT delivery and services.
Support the Data & Analytics Teams to build positive working relationships with stakeholders and promote leveraging BI solutions to assist with decision making.
Your Skillset:
 

5+ years of experience in building PowerBI dashboards and reports from scratch, ideally within a fast-paced enterprise environment.
Strong story-telling experience and design using PowerBI.
Customer / Stakeholder engagement & providing solutions through Business Intelligence.
DAX & SQL, Tabular Models.
Advanced PowerBI model optimisation using a variety of tools such as Dax Studio, ALM, Tabular Editor, etc. 
Strong knowledge of Data Warehousing concepts.
You must have unlimited working rights to be considered and be Sydney based.
